## 🔌 API Reference

### Authentication

| Method | Endpoint | Auth | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| POST | `/api/auth/register/` | ❌ | Register a new user |
| POST | `/api/auth/login/` | ❌ | Login and get tokens |
| POST | `/api/auth/logout/` | ✅ | Logout and blacklist token |
| POST | `/api/auth/token/refresh/` | ❌ | Refresh access token |
| GET | `/api/auth/me/` | ✅ | Get current user profile |

### Rooms

| Method | Endpoint | Auth | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| GET | `/api/rooms/` | ✅ | List all rooms |
| POST | `/api/rooms/` | ✅ | Create a new room |
| GET | `/api/rooms/<id>/` | ✅ | Room details + members |
| POST | `/api/rooms/<id>/join/` | ✅ | Join a room |
| POST | `/api/rooms/<id>/leave/` | ✅ | Leave a room (auto-deletes if creator) |

### Messages

| Method | Endpoint | Auth | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| POST | `/api/messages/send/` | ✅ | Send a message (async via Kafka) |
| GET | `/api/messages/?room_id=1` | ✅ | Get message history |
| GET | `/api/messages/?room_id=1&limit=20` | ✅ | Get message history with limit |
| GET | `/api/messages/?room_id=1&before_id=50` | ✅ | Cursor-based pagination |

---

## 📨 Message Flow
Client sends POST /api/messages/send/
│
▼
Django validates:
• JWT token valid?
• Room exists? (Redis cache → DB fallback)
• User is member? (Redis cache → DB fallback)
│
▼
Produce to Kafka topic "chat-messages"
│
▼
Return 202 ACCEPTED immediately
(client doesn't wait for DB write)
│
─ ─ ─ ─ ─ ┼ ─ ─ ─ ─ ─ ─ ─ ─ ─ ─ ─
│  async boundary
▼
Kafka Consumer reads message
│
├──► Save to PostgreSQL (durable storage)
│
└──► Publish to Redis channel "room:{id}"
│
▼
All subscribers receive
message in real time

---

## 🗄️ Database Schema
users
├── id (PK)
├── username (unique)
├── email
├── password (hashed)
├── is_online
└── created_at
rooms
├── id (PK)
├── name (unique)
├── creator_id (FK → users)
└── created_at
room_memberships
├── id (PK)
├── user_id (FK → users)
├── room_id (FK → rooms)
└── joined_at
[unique_together: user_id + room_id]
messages
├── id (PK)
├── room_id (FK → rooms, CASCADE)
├── sender_id (FK → users, SET_NULL)
├── content
├── timestamp
└── kafka_offset
[index: room_id + timestamp]

---

## 📦 Redis Data Structure
room:{id}:members   →  Set      {"1", "2", "3"}         Room membership
room:{id}:info      →  Hash     {name, creator_id}       Room metadata cache
room:{id}           →  Channel  Pub/Sub message channel

